This reverts commit df60bd00
added: gitignore file
added: Zeus game master no longer owned by specific user ID, now admin is module owner with #adminLogged property
added: civilians now populated at each target, new parameters for civ presence, civ unitcount and civ kill score penalty

added: civilians now populated at each target, new parameters for civ presence, civ unitcount and civ kill score penalty

Revert "f"
This reverts commit 61f70d72
fixed: score penalty for killing civs was being applied to all players
fixed: civ kill score penalty was being applied to all players

added: new parameter infantry can occupy buildings using script by Zenophon, new parameter probability of infantry being chosen to occupy a building, new parameter disable enemy air attack, new parameter punish for killing a civ (instant death), new parameter maximum number of enemy infantry barracks, default 4
fixed: merge cleanup with upstream repo
added: new parameter to disable enemy air attack fixed: de-duped a yes/no string
added: improved spawning of occupying enemy AI, now does not break up non-garrisoned groups, new parameter to configure the number of garrisoned groups to spawn at each target
added: improved spawning of occupying enemy AI, now does not break up non-garrisoned groups, new parameter to configure the number of garrisoned groups to spawn at each target
fixed: de-duplicated parameters

added: x_initcommon variables are now generated ad hoc (when armor/civ levels are set to "random"), cleaned up missing text for unlimited arty, now supports more than one civ group, new param to configure number of spawned civ groups, new param to randomize armor and civ for each target, now fixed artillery penalty for killing civs

added: new parameter d_WithLessArmor can now be randomized for each main target, new parameter number of enemy camps to capture can be configured, first enemy camp to capture will be located very near the center of the main target town, new internal scoring system uses the above randomized number of armor/capture camps and informs the user of the estimated length of the main target mission ie-- a main target with no armor and few camps may be "30 minutes" and a target with full armor and five camps will be "90 minutes" DISCLAIMER: the estimated time is based on my wild guesses, the game is not affected by the elapsed time this is just to inform the user of expected capture time
fixed: civ module locations now placed with nearestBuilding so civs will hide in buildings
fixed: civ kill punish score penalty was running on all clients,
fixed: cleanup civs and garrisoned infantry when main target is beaten, very important for server performance
fixed: civilian and garrisoned enemy units are now cleaned up when the main target is cleared (helps reduce number of objects and helps performance), fixed typos
fixed: added missing civ group count var and description
fixed: fixed civ description
added: new parameter to set maximum number of enemy camps to capture (default random 3 to 5) added: new parameter attempts to place the first enemy camp very near (10m) the center of the main target
